'''Patrick Ballantyne''' is a [[Windsor, Ontario|Windsor]]-born Canadian songwriter, guitar player and singer <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.canada.com/story.html?id=e2bad2c6-e543-4be4-843d-2ee8150d7645 |title= Songwriter Finally Gets Around to own Project |publisher=Music Biz |date=2008-08-01 |accessdate=2013-08-12}}</ref> based in Oakville, Ontario.

==Life==

Patrick was born in Windsor, ON.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.canada.com/story.html?id=e2bad2c6-e543-4be4-843d-2ee8150d7645 |title= Songwriter Finally Gets Around to Own Project |publisher=Windsor Star |date=2008-08-01 |accessdate=2013-08-12}}</ref> He is a lawyer and songwriter who now lives in Oakville, ON.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lithiummagazine.com/interview-patrick-ballantyne-april-13-2014 |title=An Interview with Patrick Ballantyne|publisher=Lithium Magazine |date=2014-04-13 |accessdate=2014-04-16}}</ref>
<ref>{{cite web|url=https://soundcloud.com/in-the-studio-on-1010/in-the-studio-podcast-may-31-2014|title=In The Studio Talks with Patrick Ballantyne|publisher=In The Studio Newstalk 1010 Radio |date=2014-05-31 |accessdate=2014-06-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://soundcloud.com/in-the-studio-on-1010/in-the-studio-podcast-may-31-2014|title=In The Studio Talks with Patrick Ballantyne|publisher=In The Studio Newstalk 1010 Radio |date=2014-05-31 |accessdate=2014-06-06}}</ref> 
<ref>{{cite web|url=http://patrickballantyne.us3.list-manage.com/track/click?u=778e02ef40219d9b8c9a92446&id=7813f391b4&e=d563963c9d|title=IFeature Interview Patrick Ballantyne|publisher=The Bride CBC Radio Windsor |date=2014-06-04 |accessdate=2014-06-06}}</ref>

==Career==

Started writing with [[Gordie Johnson]] in the 1980s <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lithiummagazine.com/interview-patrick-ballantyne-april-13-2014 |title= An Interview with Patrick Ballantyne |publisher=Lithium Magazine |date=2014-04-13 |accessdate=2014-04-16}}</ref> and has also written with [[Colin MacDonald (musician)|Colin MacDonald]] of [[The Trews]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.looklocalmagazine.com/tag/patrick-ballantyne/ |title=Local Oakville Musician to Release his Second Album |publisher=Look Local Magazine Oakville and Burlington |year=2014 |accessdate=2014-04-20}}</ref> [[Meredith Shaw]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kingstonthisweek.com/2012/04/25/shaw-is-living-her-musical-dreams |title= Shaw is Living Her Musical Dreams |publisher=Kingston This Week |date=2012-04-25| accessdate=2014-03-18}}</ref>
,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://songwriters.ca/member/MeredithShaw |title= Meredith Shaw Member Profile  |publisher= Songwriter Association of Canada |accessdate=2014-03-18}}</ref> [[Tim Chaisson]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.feelsgood.ca/profiles/blogs/tim-chaisson-s-new-album-the-other-side-review-and-interview |title= Tim Chaisson's The Other Side Review and Interview |publisher=Feels Good| date=2012-09-26 |accessdate=2014-04-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.audioblood.com/2012/12/tim-chaisson-album-release-national-tour-bumstead/|title= Tim Chaisson Album Release & National Tour (Bumstead) |publisher=Audio Blood |accessdate=2014-04-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.quipmag.com/a-chat-with-tim-chaisson/|title= A Chat with Tim Chaisson |publisher=Quip Magazine| date=2012-12-16 |accessdate=2014-04-28}}</ref> and Shane Chisholm <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.insidehalton.com/mobile/whatson/article/4467113/ |title= Oakville Musician Patrick Ballantyne Performs at The Moonshine Cafe Tomorrow |publisher=Oakville Beaver |date=2014-04-16 |accessdate=2014-04-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://audioboo.fm/boos/2265761-cm-radio-june-18-2014-chromeo-simone-denny-patrick-ballantyne-jun-19-2014#t=4m9s |title= CM Radio Chromeo, Simone Denny, Patrick Ballantyne |publisher=Canadian Musician Radio |date=2014-06-19 |accessdate=2014-06-20}}</ref>

Patrick has performed at the Toronto Centre for the Arts<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blogto.com/music/2014/05/10_under_the_radar_folk_blues_roots_venues_in_toronto/ |title= Ten Under the Radar Folk Blues Roots Venues in Toronto|publisher=Blog TO |date=2014-05-24| accessdate=2014-06-18}}</ref> as part of the Bare Bones and Up Front Series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kingstonmusicreviews.ca/BareBonesandUpFrontMeredithPatrick.html/ |title= Concert Review: Patrick Ballantyne and Meredith Shaw| publisher=Kingston Music Reviews.ca | accessdate=2014-06-18}}</ref>

=== Albums ===

*2008 Patrick Ballantyne
*2014 Days of Rain <ref>{{cite web|url=http://musicmuso.com/reviews/patrick-ballantyne-days-of-rain-album-review |title= Patrick Ballantyne Days of Rain Album Review |publisher=Music Muso| author= Kat Bagshawe |date=2014-06-20 |accessdate=2014-06-21}}</ref>

==== ''Patrick Ballantyne'' ====

Although most frequently associated with co-writing with the likes of Gordie Johnson <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.socan.ca/words-music/man-many-parts-singer-songwriter-guitarist-producer-%E2%80%94-gordie-johnson-does-it-all-and|title=A Man of Many Parts|publisher=SOCAN|year=2011|accessdate=2014-01-12|deadurl=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130730001033/http://www.socan.ca/words-music/man-many-parts-singer-songwriter-guitarist-producer-%E2%80%94-gordie-johnson-does-it-all-and|archivedate=2013-07-30|df=}}</ref> and  [[Big Sugar]],<ref>{{cite web|url= http://cadencemag.com/2011/06/big-sugar/|title=Big Sugar Back on The Scene|publisher=Cadence Magazine|date=2011-06-29|accessdate=2014-04-28}}</ref> [[The Trews]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thetelegram.com/Entertainment/2009-09-30/article-1438330/Provinces-reputation-attracts-singersongwriter/1|title=Province's Reputation Attracts Singer-Songwriter|publisher=The Telegram|date=2009-09-30|accessdate=2014-02-02}}</ref> and Tim Chaisson,<ref>http://freshindependence.com/patrick-ballantyne-oakville-ontario/</ref> Patrick released his debut solo album in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://top40-charts.com/news.php?nid=49502 |title=Writing Love Songs Doesn't Pay |publisher=Top 40 Charts.com |date=2009-06-23 |accessdate=2013-08-12}}</ref> It garnered the attention of music industry icon Ron Harwood, who placed it in top 5 independent releases of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://top40-charts.com/news.php?nid=49502 |title=Writing Love Songs Doesn't Pay |publisher=Top 40 Charts.com |date=2009-06-23 |accessdate=2013-08-12}}</ref>

==== ''Days of Rain'' ====

Released in June 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lithiummagazine.com/interview-patrick-ballantyne-april-13-2014 |title= An Interview with Patrick Ballantyne |publisher=Lithium Magazine |date=2014-04-16 |accessdate=2014-04-22}}</ref> The release show was held at Musideum in Toronto.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://musideum.com/concerts/patrick-ballantyne/ |title=Patrick Ballantyne at Musideum |publisher=Musideum |accessdate=2014-06-12}}</ref> The album differs from the first album in that it has more instrumentation (piano and string) than the first release<ref>{{cite web|url=http://audioboo.fm/boos/2265761-cm-radio-june-18-2014-chromeo-simone-denny-patrick-ballantyne-jun-19-2014#t=4m9s |title= CM Radio Chromeo, Simone Denny, Patrick Ballantyne |publisher=Canadian Musician Radio |date=2014-06-19 |accessdate=2014-06-20}}</ref>

*The title track "King of the Road" was co-written with [[Meredith Shaw]] and [[Gordie Johnson]]. The song originally appeared in a different incarnation on [[Meredith Shaw]]'s EP "Place Called Happy".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://audioboo.fm/boos/2265761-cm-radio-june-18-2014-chromeo-simone-denny-patrick-ballantyne-jun-19-2014#t=4m9s |title= CM Radio Chromeo, Simone Denny, Patrick Ballantyne |publisher=Canadian Musician Radio |date=2014-06-19 |accessdate=2014-06-20}}</ref>
*The lyric video for "Wrestling with the Devil" was featured by Snob's Music as a Friday Find <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.snobsmusic.net/2014/06/friday-find-patrick-ballantyne.html |title=Friday Find:Patrick Ballantyne|publisher=Snob's Music| date=2014-06-06 |accessdate=2014-06-20}}</ref> and as a Mute Music Moment of the Day <ref>{{cite web|url=http://mutemag.com/?p=6239|title=Mute Music Moment of the Day Wrestling with the Devil Patrick Ballantyne|publisher=Mutemag|accessdate=2014-06-22}}</ref>
* Re-released January 2015 under Northwood Records' label

==== ''Hit A Month'' ====

In 2015, Patrick Ballantyne started the sardonically titled "hitamonth.com" project, aiming to release a single every month for the year.

==== Songwriting Credits ====
* 2012 wrote "No One Came" on No One Came - Shane Chisholm

==== Collaborations ====
*2014 Co-wrote "Slide" ([[Meredith Shaw]], EP Hardest Goodbye) <ref>{{cite web|url=http://lithiummagazine.com/interview-meredith-shaw-%E2%80%93-march-5-2014 |title= An Interview with Meredith Shaw |publisher=Lithium Magazine |date=2014-03-05 |accessdate=2014-11-07}}</ref>
*2013 Co-wrote "Call it a Night" ([[Meredith Shaw]], EP Trouble)  <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maritimevinyl.ca/2013/05/meredith-shaw-trouble-review_28.html |title= Meredith Shaw Trouble Review |publisher=Maritime Vinyl |date=2013-05-28 |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref>
*2013 Co-wrote "Beat This Heart" ([[Tim Chaisson]], The Other Side),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.magisto.com/2014/02/23/battle-of-the-fans-meet-tim-chaisson/|title= Battle of the Fans: meet Tim Chaisson |publisher=Magisto |date=2014-02-23 |accessdate=2014-02-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bumstead.com/tim-chaisson-releases-video-for-beat-this-heart-national-tour-with-poor-young-things-kicks-off-october-26th//|title= Tim Chaisson Releases Video For ‘Beat This Heart’, National Tour With Poor Young Things Kicks Off October 26th |publisher=Bumstead |date=2012-10-04 |accessdate=2014-03-22}}</ref> 
*2013 Co-wrote "Blast Your Way Out" ([[Tim Chaisson]], The Other Side) <ref>{{cite web|url=http://digitalrodeo.com/news/music-reviews-jaida-dreyer-tim-chaisson-and-no-justice/|title= Music Reviews Jaida Dreyer and Tim Chaisson |publisher=Digital Rodeo |accessdate=2014-02-20}}</ref>
*2012 Co-wrote "Love Song for You" and "Livin' the Dream" (Shane Chisholm, No One Came)
*2011 Co-wrote ""So Good," "King of the Road," "There's No Tellin',", "Breakin'," "Happy," Little Fishy," "Acted Badly," "Girls Who Believe" ([[Meredith Shaw]], Place Called Happy)
*2011 Co-wrote "Sweet Little Thing" ([[Wide Mouth Mason]], No Bad Days)
*2007 Co-wrote "One of These Days" and "Three Legged Race" ([[Grady (band)|Grady]], A Cup of Cold Poison)
*2005 Co-wrote "Poor Ol' Broken Hearted Me" ([[The Trews]]. [[Den of Thieves (album)|Den of Thieves]])
*2001 Co-wrote "All Hell for a Basement" ([[Big Sugar]], [[Brothers and Sisters, Are You Ready?]])
*1998 Co-wrote "Cop a Plea," "Girl Watcher," "Kickin' Stones" and "Heart Refuse to Pound" (Big Sugar, [[Heated (Big Sugar album)|Heated]])
*1996 Co-wrote "Gone For Good", "Empty Head", and "[[If I Had My Way (song)|If I Had My Way]]" (Big Sugar, [[Hemi-Vision]])

====Other Music Credits====
